  "time_ut": 1658823356,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dbd\u0db6\u0dbd\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A place to distribute fuel without fuss",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The fuel received by the Manampitiya fuel station is jointly implemented by the drivers association, the tricycle association and the employees of the Manampitiya fuel station with the involvement of the police to distribute the fuel fairly to everyone.",
        "Manampitiya Police Station Commander Inspector Asela Sarath Kumara and the police officers together received six hundred and six hundred liters of petrol brought to the Manampitiya petrol station at 9:30 pm on the 25th and continued to give it to all the motorcycles, tricycles and cars in the relevant queue. To the mothers. A system was also set up to easily get fuel for the pet vehicles carrying various patients and for special essential institutions as well as for individuals without queuing.",
        "An iron gate fence has also been installed in front of the Manampitiya petrol station and at one time five motorbikes. Three three-wheelers and two cars will be admitted to the petrol station and delivered from there.",
        "The workers of the Manampitiya Police Fuel Station as well as the Lorry Drivers Association appreciate the sacrifices made by the people working in the queue to provide the daily supply of diesel and petrol until the end of the fuel queue.",
        "According to the QR code system, Manampitiya petrol station provided fuel from the 25th, but after 12 midnight for almost an hour, QR. Due to an error in the system, there was a disruption in the fuel distribution, where the employees of the fuel station as well as the police intervened and provided fuel continuously until 7:00 AM without causing any inconvenience to the people in the queue.",
        "The association states that it is an opportunity to remove the police and lorry drivers together before distributing the fuel to the drunken people who roam near and in front of the Manampitiya and Sevanapitiya petrol stations during the day and at night and then succeed in the fuel distribution activities.",
        "The Manampitiya police have been praised by the officers of the government institutions for giving the necessary fuel to the doctors of the Polonnaruwa General Hospital, the lawyers of the Polonnaruwa Court, the wildlife officers of the Manampitiya Wildlife Office as well as the special security forces, the principals and teachers without waiting in line."
      ],
